            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By authors. In fission, the two fragments are emitted",
                "back to back with equal momenta in any direction in the",
                "C.-M. System.  This momentum distribution is converted",
                "in the laboratory system into a narrow cone centered in",
                "the beam direction. Only fragments emitted forward and",
                "backward in the C.-M.  System can pass the fragment",
                "separator, and those emitted in directions",
                "perpendicular to the beam direction cannot be",
                "observed.  Low energy fission is separable by delta-E",
                "measurements, by detecting one of the fragments only in",
                "the restricted phase space of forward emitted fragments",
                "at the largest momenta."
              ]
            }
          ],
